Doc Spatz- Went to #44, found you up to your old tricks.  I realize it may not be my place to say anything (I've had my &quot;problems&quot; conveying my thoughts on here), but I think if you try to restrain yourself and attempt to be more sensitive to the feelings of others, especially vets, you'll find fewer people reacting negatively to you (like I did a while back).  On this thread you've been pretty &quot;cool&quot; of late.  You've watched your tone, so to speak. I really appreciate the more civil discourse this particular thread has been taking lately, and would hate to see it revert back to the name-calling and nastiness of the not-so-distant past.  It's okay to be crazy, but let's not inflict our craziness on others.  I'm trying.  How 'bout you?  
